##24 hours after New Year's Eve in Wuhan: 15 Hubei Diaries from the outbreak

The FAIR2

Function description, the last minute of every day life school, we will eventually change the direction of the tide.

- This is article 1,175 of the Pliocene. -

Sayingsï¼š

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, 24 hours after the New Year's Eve, the city of Wuhan has been closed for 3 days.

New Year's Eve Bell, people are expressing the concern for Wuhan, as well as the entire Hubei.

For more specific information, the Press Office of the Pliocene epoch found residents in Hubei Province, first-line medical workers and construction workers, engineers at the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, couples stuck in a highway..

This is not only Wuhan, but also Hubei 24 hours after New Year's Eve.

15 Hubei Diaries from the outbreak

SELF-DESCRIPTION: Readers and friends of the Miocene facies

Wuhan | engineer, Vulcan Mountain Hospital

"24-hour construction,

Until the work is done."

@ I'm 40 and I'm smiling

At present, the Construction Force in Wuhan is concentrating on the construction of Huoshenshan Hospital.

Received the task that moment is very nervous, rest during the New Year, can not recruit people is the most nervous, we are in accordance with 1200 yuan a day knot recruitment.

24-HOUR NON-STOP CONSTRUCTION, construction management staff 50 people at the scene, 100 sets of excavators excavation.

At present, the supporting works of water supply pipelines have been completed and put into place, and the roads are being laid.

You don't start work, you don't finish work. 24-hour raid, shift change, field excavator replacement.

It's GonNa take more than that. The target is set to go live on February 3rd.

Think of the hospital staff are playing with their lives, we are not afraid.

And the sooner we finish this, the MORE LIVES WE'LL SAVE!

Xiaogan, Hubei | Yoga teacher

"twenty-four hours after New Year's Eve,

2,000 men and I sent supplies to the hospital."

@ Miss Su, 36

On New Year's Eve, after I finished my New Year's Eve dinner, I saw a friend of a NURSE'S CIRCLE OF FRIENDS:

"There's nothing in the suits and the goggles. "

A ask just know, Xiaogan built a new quarantine area, doctors and nurses are on, supplies can not keep up.

They only gave out one mask each. Actually, masks change in three or four hours, but they only have one.

The doctor was dressed in scrubs, thin. I can't drink water, and I'm afraid if I go to the bathroom, my clothes will burst and I won't wear them.

A colleague of my aunt's sent a video:

The father was afraid his daughter wouldn't be protected, so he did it at home.

I work in a Yoga Studio. There are hundreds of students in the group. So I sent a message calling on everyone to gather supplies for the front-line staff.

Four groups of 500 were built, one by one, and the first wave of supplies was found.

When we went to the hospital this morning to deliver supplies, the head nurse picked us up.

He took off his gloves and tried to shake my hand. I was afraid to shake it.

He said don't worry, we're all clean.

Everybody's scared. So Am I.

But when the paramedics are safe, so are we.

Secretary of the Village Committee | Wuhan, Hubei Province

"How to keep the people in their homes,

I'm working on it."

@ Anon, 54

I am the secretary of the village in the Yuancheng District of Wuhan. No cases have been found in the village so far.

I'm on duty at the village committee on New Year's Eve. I told the village wechat group not to send New Year greetings on New Year's Day twenty-nine, but I was still afraid of what might happen.

Good thing we didn't see anyone on the road. Everyone is still quite self-conscious, plan to give them a little bonus in the group.

After Wuhan closed the city, the district began to close the access to the surrounding counties and cities, build temporary shelters, 24-hour man-on-duty, do not allow access.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Every day four village cadres and 10 central household heads went to each household to check the feverish people who had returned from the downtown area and reported the data at 3 p.m.

Some villagers do not care: "risk a few big things, not dead. "

I guess I was still afraid of death. I asked him if any of his family had come back from Hankou or Wuchang.

The day before yesterday the street pulled down the mask, but each person only enough to issue one, stock shortage.

Today, the street leaders sent over the thermometers, two for each village. That's enough.

Now eat the food is enough, the village into the wax month began to prepare new year goods, wax fish wax meat, fish cake meat cake.

There are Chinese cabbage, Chinese cabbage, carrot and white radish in the garden.

What is more difficult is how to make the people stay indoors for more than five days and ten days. We are trying to find a way.

Wuhan, Wuchang District | engineer
"There are rumors of people falling to the ground without symptoms,
And the word gets around."
@ An anonymous wmls, 29

Wuhan, Wuchang District | engineer

"There are rumors of people falling to the ground without symptoms,

And the word gets around."

@ An anonymous wmls, 29

Last night, when the countdown to the Spring Festival gala, our side of the circle of friends are asking for help information.

My company is also in Wuhan, every day will count the status of employees, whether fever and whether there are difficulties in need of help.

Everyone's back to normal every day.

The rumor about the asymptomatic fall is coming from our neighborhood.

Is the audio, said 120 came directly covered with white cloth towed away, the security took a loudspeaker said do not go out, in fact, not.

However, the flow out, followed by the spread of Wechat Group, and added a number of unknown causes in Wuhan unknown date of the fall video, the more spread more and more powerful.

Then yesterday there was the Wuhan version of Xiaotangshan site errors to be rebuilt, but also refuted the rumors.

Mask at home, the day before yesterday went to five pharmacies, masks and alcohol are gone.

Wuhan, Hubei | publishing editor
"The three of US ate separately
Sleep in separate rooms."
@ Number 10, age 25

I didn't have New Year's Eve dinner last night. Mom and I spent it alone.

My Dad was on duty at the railroad station last night. Because there are passing vehicles to be deployed, many supplies are also transported by rail.

To prevent cross-contamination, we also wear masks at home, except in the shower and at bedtime.

Separate meals and sleeping in separate rooms are practiced in the home. Everyone use their own bowl, spoon, plate, make a good meal with communal chopsticks.

Three separate beds, two separate bathrooms, one for Dad.

The streets were silent, with the occasional sound of ambulances.

Tomorrow Motor vehicles will be banned, ordinary people at home health is still good, if sick really feel no recourse.

I've hoarded everything I could think of. Masks, 84 sterile solution, finger clips for oxygen levels (which can drop below normal if the lungs are infected) , and goggles.

What is most in short supply are masks, disinfectants and medicines. I bought it on Taobao, but I don't know if I can ship it, if I can get it.

Suizhou, Hubei | homebound entrepreneur
"On the day of the siege,
I left a note for my husband."
@Miss Yang

We passed by Wuhan on our way home from Shanghai.

Around 2:00 p.m. on the 23rd. The expressway in and out of Wuhan is still open. And then at the next intersection, they're all repatriated.

Two KLICKS. We've been walking for five hours.

I don't know if I can get out, I don't open my windows, I don't talk to people, and I wear a mask in my car.

I've been leaving messages for my husband for hours, and I've never felt so scared.

My husband didn't say anything after he saw it. He just kept holding my hand.

The situation in Wuhan is even more serious.

You can't buy cabbages, says roommate, a college student.

Another roommate, who lives close to Hankou station and the south China Seafood Market, could only grab a radish.

The city was closed at 2400 hours yesterday, and there was no one on the streets of the city centre.

But the small areas around Hubei have only been taken seriously in the past two days.

It wasn't until a few minutes ago that our small town began to advertise not to drop by.

There are already people in this town under quarantine.

Wuhan, Hubei | employees of state owned enterprises
"My husband has a fever. "
@ Nana, 33

About three days ago, my husband started to feel sick, shivering and having a sore throat.

He had a fever of 38.8 at 7:00 last night, and he lived alone in his study, isolated himself, while I cooked and brought in food and took care of my 6-year-old daughter.

My daughter, with her innocent, happy face, didn't quite understand the situation. I tried to protect her, but I don't think I can right now.

The husband also does not know oneself is the pneumonia or the ordinary infection inflammation, the symptom does not see completely.

We worried that going to the hospital would increase the risk of cross-infection, and for days and nights, he felt even worse.

Just went to the designated hospital, too many people to line up.

Dare not stay too long, changed a general hospital, the doctor checked blood can not judge, let him go home to continue to observe.

I've decided to take the children to the old man tonight before the traffic ban. I'll stay and take care of my husband.

Call the Community Hospital tomorrow and keep canvassing, no matter what the results.

Migrant workers from Wuhan, Hubei Province
"Two days,
My co-workers and I helped with six deliveries."
@ Mr. Lee, 33

My family is in Henan, people work in Wuhan. And drain pipes and drains, and missing manhole covers.

See the Fire God mountain construction site need trucks, excavators, the boss also let us volunteer to help, we have six trucks, on the friends circle message, said can transport goods.

Two days now, six trips of medical supplies.

There weren't enough masks, so I went to a few pharmacies with five of my co-workers, and we ended up with only seven.

But we were running from morning to night, and once back to the dorm, we would wash our hands and faces, remind each other to take our temperature, and then use the dryer to dry our damp masks.

On New Year's Eve, a few of our workmates gathered together and cooked some dishes: Fried eggs with garlic sprouts, beef, mutton..

No one watches the gala, it's all news: How many cases have gone up, and where are the new outbreaks.

Good thing we don't have a confirmed case.

I still miss my daughter-in-law, she said, someone asked me why my father didn't go back. The daughter replied:

"Now a lot of people in Wuhan have a cold. Dad is over there giving medicine to people who have a cold. "

My daughter is so sensible.

We all have feelings about the city: Like it too early Ah, hot dry noodles AH, Wuhan People's Voice Ah... feel that we speak quite funny.

I feel sorry for you. I hope you feel better soon.

Ensch, Hubei | nurse

"because of the road closures,

Some of the doctors and nurses couldn't make it back."

@ Max, 23

Eleven confirmed in Ensch.

Now our hospital about seven o'clock in the morning, doctors and nurses at the door of the people in and out of the body temperature.

The hospital is in urgent need of protective equipment. Masks N95 and surgical masks are given out in limited quantities.

We are the clinical support center, assisting other clinical departments in some of their work.

The off-duty doctors and nurses had to rush back to the city to be on call.

But some people were so far away that they returned to find the road closed and there were no cars.

Hospitals have canteens, meals are guaranteed.

The city's public transport has been suspended, a self-organized car to send us to and from work, really warm.

The owner of the car is part of the hospital family, there are also some anxious people in society, generally speaking, not many.

Wuhan, Hubei | editor
"doctors can't be left alone,
I call upon tens of thousands of people to drive them to and from work."
@ Cavan, 30

I was on Sabbatical in South Africa on the 14th, and I knew about it, but I didn't think much of it.

On the 22nd, I returned to Wuhan and said to my wife, "Wuhan is too big a city to close. ".

Didn't think I was really jinxed, the next day on the closure of the city, the family unit isolation.

A friend told me a doctor couldn't get to and from work right after the road was closed. I decided to do it. I couldn't let the doctor do it alone.

It was a small crowd. We were one-on-one.

All car owners must wear face masks and goggles if possible. Carry alcohol or disinfectant with you at all times.

Each doctor is ventilated for 40 minutes, and then the next.

In the process, it began to take on a life of its own

Add in the doctor, 400 people or less, and it's up to a few thousand.

Yesterday alone, I built more than 23 groups, close to 10,000 people, and I can't even count the number of doctors I've transported.

New Year's Eve I have been back in the group of News, my wife also helped me manage two groups. Instant noodles for New Year's Eve dinner.

Without the concept of the first day of the Lunar New Year, I realized when I saw someone posting a joke on my friends'circle:

It's New Year's Eve. It's the Spring Festival gala.

I feel like it's been a long day, the phone hasn't stopped ringing, and I haven't had much sleep.

But the government has just announced that, starting tomorrow, all cars will be off the streets, saying the government will be unified.

Well, we've done our part.

Wuhan, Hubei | reporter, freezing point weekly
"I'm not afraid to be on the line. "
@ Wang Jiaxing, 25
I've been living in a bit of a trance. Was it the 24th yesterday?

Yesterday, I got the photo of my colleague in Vulcan Mountain. I didn't go to bed until 3:00 am.

I myself am from Wuhan. I went home on the 18th for the Spring Festival. I also wanted to report on the pneumonia, but I didn't expect it to be so serious.

Until 7:00 a.m. on the 23rd, when I opened my phone and saw the city sealed off.
My first reaction was to go to the railway station to have a look, when I went to find that the police had pulled up the human wall.

There are a lot of people lined up to return tickets, to take the paper ticket must be returned to the artificial window, the black pressure of a piece.

Then I went to the market, and the vegetables were gone by 10:00.

Wanted to pick up the camera and take a picture, so the security guard came over and tried to erase it.
I told him in Wuhan dialect that I was a student in Wuhan, to do social research, he did not.
My mom would stop me at first, saying, "you're not the only one doing the interview. ".

But I'm not afraid to be on the line.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Wuhan Wuchang | market sales

"The first step is to close the city,

The second step is to close the bridge, and now the vehicle."

@ Dayun, 29

I haven't left the house in four days. Here's what we've got:

It's the first day of the New Year, but it's very quiet downstairs.

Two weeks before the Chinese New Year, Wuhan was very lively.

January 16, my family also organized a family reunion, eat together, singing, did not know the severity of the disease.

My sister-in-law was a medical worker in the third-grade Hospital of Wuhan. She was on the front line in the war of resistance against Japan.

Special occasion. She's basically in the hospital now. Her 6-year-old son cries for his mother every day.

My sister-in-law hasn't called him, and they don't even have time to eat, and they don't even have to go to the bathroom.

We told him -- "Mother Florida is on the move.

We can understand: medical staff can only go in the front, in order to help Wuhan tide over the difficulties.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Teacher | Primary School, Wuhan, Hubei
"We called 3,000 students. "
That's pretty fancy

I worked as a teacher in a primary school for 3,000 people. When things got serious, all the teachers called each student one by one to inform them of the extension of the holiday and the specific starting date.

It was slowly getting worse -- I started getting 100 masks. There is a garbage can at the gate of the residential area for collecting discarded masks.

Wuchang Castle peak | graduate student

"The lights are on in every house in the community,

But there's no sound."

@ Who am I, 25 years old

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This is a picture of the Wuhan Station the day before the siege. It's empty.

I am still in Graduate School, January 17 holiday, originally the eighth day to return to Beijing to do experiments, now is certainly impossible.

Aoyama's side is not a major disaster area, the number of confirmed cases is unknown, official figures do not specify the region.

Public Transport was stopped and people wore masks when they went out to take out the rubbish.

I've never been to a hospital. I'm afraid to go. Because of overcrowding at the designated hospitals.

A lot of people are freaking out.

One of my sisters, one day she's panicking, the next day she's nauseous, and she thinks she fits the bill.

I talked to my psych classmate, said it was stress.

I closed the city that night did not sleep, out the news on the box horse orders, stockpiled for more than a week of food.

Now all the restaurant resources are going to the paramedics.
I thought it would be nice to close the city. I'll be scolded anyway.

Wuhan Railway Station the day before the siege

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Railway Station the day before the siege

Someone I met 10 years ago who hasn't spoken to me in more than five years sent me a message:

"How are you? I remember you are from Wuhan. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I cried. One second, I see a lot of abuse on Weibo.

Now I look out of the window, every home is lit, but no one in the community also no car sound, quiet enough to hear the voice of air conditioning.

My Dad just went down to take out the trash, bought a bottle of soy sauce, and now he's working out.

My Dad's in a good mood. I think he thinks everything's GonNa be okay.

I believe it, too.
